      "content": "hey, i'm trying to build this little tool to catch flaky tests in our CI pipeline. basically i need a function `detect_flakiness(func, n_runs=10)` that returns `True` if the function is non-deterministic (gives different results or sometimes fails) and `False` if it's stable. \n\nanyway, i've got some tests i need it to pass. can u write the function for me?\n\n```python\nimport random\n\n# Test 1: A flaky test (sometimes returns True, sometimes False)\ndef flaky_test():\n    return random.choice([True, False])\n\n# Test 2: A stable test that always returns False\ndef stable_test():\n    return False\n\n# Test 3: A stable test that always returns True\ndef stable_pass():\n    return True\n\n# My validation logic\ndef run_tests(detector):\n    # should detect the flaky one\n    assert detector(flaky_test) == True, \"Failed to detect flaky_test\"\n    # should not flag the stable one\n    assert detector(stable_test) == False, \"False positive on stable_test\"\n    # should not flag the other stable one\n    assert detector(stable_pass) == False, \"False positive on stable_pass\"\n    print(\"All tests passed!\")\n\n# detector = detect_flakiness\n# run_tests(detector)\n```\n\nmake sure it works with these.",
